sql:
SELECT DISTINCT school_name, city, state, metro_type
FROM schools
ORDER BY school_name, city, state;

SELECT schools.school_name, donations.total_donations
FROM schools
JOIN donations ON schools.school_id = donations.school_id
WHERE schools.is_public = 1 AND donations.total_donations > (
        SELECT AVG(total_donations) FROM donations
    );

SELECT SUM(total_donations) FROM donations
JOIN schools ON donations.school_id = schools.school_id
WHERE schools.school_name = 'XYZ School';

external_knowledge:
- "drops of charity" metaphorically refers to donations;
- "wells of public education" symbolizes public schools;
- "weathering the storm of extreme poverty" is a metaphor for schools facing severe poverty conditions.

sql:
SELECT SUM(total_donations) AS total_wealth_2011
FROM donations
WHERE year = 2011;

external_knowledge:
urgent needs in math and science education: refers to resources related to Math & Science that are marked as urgently needed; 
economic hardship: refers to the varying levels of poverty among different schools; 
cities: specifically urban metropolitan areas in this context. 
average donors per donation: calculated as the sum of individual donors divided by the number of donations.
